        "text": "*[Bug 19006] New: as.POSIX{ct,lt}(&lt;character&gt;) fails for \"Inf\"*\n<https:\/\/bugs.r-project.org\/show_bug.cgi?id=19006>\n\n            Bug ID: 19006\n           Summary: as.POSIX{ct,lt}(&lt;character&gt;) fails for \"Inf\"\n           Product: R\n           Version: R 4.5.x\n          Hardware: All\n                OS: All\n            Status: NEW\n          Severity: minor\n          Priority: P5\n         Component: Low-level\n          Assignee: <mailto:R-core@R-project.org|R-core@R-project.org>\n          Reporter: <mailto:maechler@stat.math.ethz.ch|maechler@stat.math.ethz.ch>\n\nEven though we have made progress of allowing datetime objects of class\n`POSIXct`, `POSIXlt` and `Date` to behave more like numbers (POSIXct and Date\nbeing internally stored as numbers anyway) and consequently even allow the\nborder (and completely abstract) cases of `-Inf` and `+Inf` for them,\nexperimenting with the valid wishlist Bug 18989 lead me to find another\ninconsistency, i.e., bug.\nExample code:\n```\n## as.POSIXlt(\"Inf\") should work\n(Ilt &lt;- as.POSIXlt(II &lt;- c(-Inf,Inf))) #  \"-Inf\" \"Inf\"\n Ict &lt;- as.POSIXct(II)\ncII &lt;- as.character(II)\n\nstopifnot(exprs = {\n    identical(II, as.numeric(Ilt))\n    identical(II, as.numeric(Ict))\n    identical(Ilt, as.POSIXlt(Ict))\n    identical(cII, as.character(Ict))\n    identical(cII, as.character(Ilt))\n})\n``` \nall fine; just demo'ing what works already, nicely.\nHowever, these fail simply (and clearly where):\n```\nas.POSIXct(cII)\nas.POSIXlt(cII)\n```\nboth giving the same error, e.g., directly also from\n```\n&gt; as.POSIXct(Inf)\nError in as.POSIXlt.character(x, tz, ...) : \n  character string is not in a standard unambiguous format\n&gt;\n```\n\nIt seems this has not broken any code till now, as nobody had reported it;\nhence it is not an urgent problem for people using R to work with data.\nStill I strongly believe the two calls above should give `Ict` and `Ilt`\nrespectively, even if only for internal consistency \/ symmetry.",
